#Text=[0728] Example 3a, Step 1: N,O-Dimethylhydroxylamine hydrochloride (5.7 g) was suspended in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 (80 mL) and cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. prior to the addition of 2.0 M AlMe.sub.3 (29.1 mL) in hexane.
#Text=The mixture was warmed to rt over 1 h, then cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. prior to the addition of benzyl (1R,2S,5R)-7-oxo-6-oxa-bicyclo[3.2.1]octan-2-ylcar-bamate (8.0 g) in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 (80 mL).
#Text=After 5 h at 0.degree.
#Text=C., the reaction was quenched with a 10% Rochelle salt solution and extracted with EtOAc (2.times.).
#Text=The organic extracts were combined, washed with brine, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting residue was dissolved in DMF (100 mL) prior to the addition of imidazole (1.97 g) and TBSCl (4.4 g).
#Text=The reaction was stirred for 12 h at rt and then partitioned between EtOAc and a saturated brine solution.
#Text=The organic phases were combined, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered, and concentrated in vacuo.
#Text=The residue was purified by flash chromatography to afford benzyl (1S,2R,4R)-4-(tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy)-2-(methoxy(met-hyl)carbamoyl)cyclohexylcarbamate (11.2 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=451.3.
#Text=[0729] Example 3a, Step 2: Benzyl (1S,2R,4R)-4-(tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy-)-2-(methoxy(methyl)carbamoyl)cyclohexylcarbamate (4.0 g) was dissolved in THF (40 mL) and cooled to -22.degree.
#Text=C. prior to the addition of 1.6 M MeLi (14.5 mL) in Et.sub.2O.
#Text=After 40 min at -22.degree.
#Text=C., the reaction was quenched with 0.5 N HCl solution and extracted with EtOAc (2.times.).
#Text=The organic extracts were combined, washed with brine, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting residue was purified by flash chromatography to afford benzyl (1S,2R,4R)-2-acetyl-4-(-tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy)cyclohexylcarbamate (5.7 g).
#Text=MS found: (M +H).sup.+=406.3.
#Text=[0730] Example 3a, Step 3: Methyltriphenylphosphonium bromide (1.2 g) was suspended in toluene (16 mL) prior to the addition of 0.5M potassium bis(trimethylsilyl)amide (5.8 mL) in toluene.
#Text=After 1 h, this solution was cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. prior to the addition of benzyl (1S,2R,4R)-2-acetyl-4-(tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy)cyclohexylcarbamate (660 mg) in toluene (5.4 mL).
#Text=After 20 min at 0.degree.
#Text=C., the reaction was quenched with saturated NH.sub.4Cl solution and extracted with EtOAc (2.times.).
#Text=The organic extracts were combined, washed with brine, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting residue was purified by flash chromatography to afford benzyl (1S,2S,4R)-4-(tert-buty-ldimethylsilyloxy)-2-(prop-1-en-2-yl)cyclohexylcarbamate (380 mg).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=404.2.
#Text=[0731] Example 3a, Step 4: Benzyl (1S,2S,4R)-4-(tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy-)-2-(prop-1-en-2-yl)cyclohexylcarbamate (4.8 g) in MeOH (40 mL) was charged with 10% Pd/C, Degussa (600 mg).
#Text=The reaction flask was evacuated and then back-filled with hydrogen; this was repeated three more times.
#Text=The reaction was stirred under 1 atm of H.sub.2 for 4 h and then filtered and concentrated to provide (1S,2S,4R)-4-(tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy)-2-i-sopropylcyclohexanamine (2.9 g).
#Text=MS (ES+)=272.3 (M+H).sup.+.
#Text=[0732] Example 3a, Step 5: (1S,2S,4R)-4-(Tert-butyldimethylsilyloxy)-2-iso-propylcyclohexanamine (2.9 g) was dissolved in DMF (36 mL) and cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. prior to the addition of N-Cbz methionine (5.5 g), 4-methyl morpholine (3.8 g), and BOP (8.7 g).
#Text=The reaction was stirred for 12 h at rt and then partitioned between EtOAc and 1N HCl solution.
#Text=The organic phases were combined, washed with saturated NaHCO.sub.3 and brine, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered, and concentrated in vacuo.
#Text=The residue was purified by flash chromatography to afford benzyl (S)-1-((1S,2S,4R)-4-(te-rt-butyldimethylsilyloxy)-2-isopropylcyclohexylamino)-4-(methylthio)-1-oxo-butan-2-ylcarbamate (5.3 g).
